    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>In some localities in some localities up to 15 cm of snow has fallen. The small quantity of fresh snow and the wind slabs must be evaluated with care and prudence in all aspects. Wind slabs represent the main danger.</highlights>
      <comment>Down to 1200 m snow has fallen since Saturday in some localities. The wind slabs of last week represent the main danger. The wind slabs must be evaluated with care and prudence in all aspects. They can be released very easily. These have formed especially in gullies and bowls, and behind abrupt changes in the terrain. Weak layers exist in the old snowpack on northwest, north and northeast facing slopes. Avalanches can be triggered in the old snowpack reach large size in particular on northwest, north and northeast facing slopes. &lt;br/> Snow sport activities outside marked and open pistes call for experience and great restraint.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
      <comment>The small quantity of fresh snow of the weekend and in particular the wind slabs formed by the strong wind are lying on the unfavourable surface of an old snowpack. &lt;br/> The strong wind has transported some snow. Individual weak layers exist in the old snowpack especially on shady slopes. Avalanches can in some places be released in deep layers in particular on northwest, north and northeast facing slopes.</comment>
    </snowpackStructure>
    <travelAdvisory/>
    <tendency>
      <tendencyType>steady</tendencyType>
